HEADWORD: Pellibranchiata
<hw>Pel`li*bran`chi*a"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. <ets>pellis</ets> garment + <ets>branchia</ets> a
gill.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of Nudibranchiata, in
which the mantle itself serves as a gill.</def>⟦br⟧
